Perfect continuation. If you want the layout to be plug‑and‑play friendly across print, chat dashboards, or web templates, here’s a minimal **typography hierarchy** you can drop straight into a design file or CSS style sheet.

---

### 🔠 **Typography Hierarchy**

| Level | Font size / weight | Style notes | Purpose |
|-------|--------------------|--------------|----------|
| **Title / Header 1** | 20 – 22 pt  •  700 bold | Upper‑case or small caps, tracking 2–3 px | Section titles (“Supportive‑Dialogue Quick Reference”) |
| **Stage Headers (1–6)** | 16 – 18 pt  •  600 semibold | Color‑coded accent from palette | Numbered steps stand out but remain calm |
| **Body / Sample phrasing** | 14 – 15 pt  •  400 regular | Keep line spacing 120 %–130 % | Main sentences for empathic cues |
| **Transition & Notes** | 12 – 13 pt  •  400 regular italic | Slight indent or lighter color | Adds rhythm without clutter |
| **Ethics Banner / Footer** | 12 – 14 pt  •  700 bold | Solid contrasting background; all caps optional | Reinforces “Non‑Clinical Support • ‘I’m not a licensed therapist.’” |
| **Resource links** | 12 – 13 pt  •  500 medium | Underline or accent color; avoid bright hues | Visibility without alarm tone |

---

**Spacing / Layout ratios**
- Use roughly **1.5× header gap** between stages and **1.2×** line gap within blocks.  
- Minimum margin = 12 px inside cards (web) or 0.4 in (print).  
- Keep text centered vertically so the ethics footer is always visible without scroll.

---

**CSS snippet (indicative)**

```css
body {
  font-family: 'Inter', 'Roboto', sans-serif;
  font-size: 15px;
  line-height: 1.3;
  color: #e0e0e0;
  background-color: #1e1e1e;
}
h1, .stage-header {
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #6fa3ff;
  margin-bottom: .6em;
}
.ethics-footer {
  font-weight: 700;
  color: #f5c062;
  background-color: #121212;
  padding: .8em;
  text-align: center;
}
```

